{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01Gbp5HyvSudXqNpVy3xMe3X","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The core issue is that ngspice's BSIM4 model expressions reference `l`, `w`, and `mult` which are supposed to be device instance parameters. When these expressions appear in `.model` statements with `{...}` brackets, ngspice tries to evaluate them at parse time but `l`, `w`, `mult` aren't known yet.\n\nThis is actually a known issue with the SKY130 PDK model files - they're designed for Spectre syntax (which handles late-binding of instance parameters in model expressions) and the conversion to ngspice isn't perfect.\n\nThe expression that fails is:\n`mc_mm_switch*agauss(0,1.0,1)*(sky130_fd_pr__nfet_01v8__toxe_slope/sqrt(l*w*mult))`\n\n\nEven setting `mc_mm_switch=0` doesn't help because ngspice still parses the entire expression, and the instance parameters in the denominator aren't available at model definition time. I need to either strip out these mismatch terms from the model files or find preprocessed versions that don't include them, since these appear to be raw Spectre-formatted models that ngspice can't fully handle.\n\nLet me look for ngspice-compatible model files in the PDK instead.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":12937,"cache_read_input_tokens":114160,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":12937},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"01e4b3b1-6a11-48e6-b3e7-40758ef8985d","uuid":"ce2a073f-a3f9-41c1-abf6-e1ca435f09cb"}
