{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01JcEfqrMEXkA7M38WzD4Vyj","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Same result. Vth = 1.022V for the PFET. This seems like the BSIM4 model is computing a Vth of ~1V for this device geometry.\n\nBut this makes operation at 1.8V very difficult — you need |Vgs| > 1.0V to turn on, leaving only 0.8V of headroom.\n\nActually, I think the issue might be that the BSIM4 Vth includes body effect. For a PMOS, the N-well body is typically connected to VDD. In our test, the body is connected to VDD (drain gate vdd vdd). \n\nLet me recalculate: with Vgs = 0.6V, the gate is at 1.2V and source at 1.8V, so Vgs = -0.6V. The body is also at 1.8V, same as the source, meaning Vbs = 0 and there's no body effect. But ngspice is reporting Vth = +1.022V, which is odd since PMOS threshold voltage should be negative — it's probably reporting the magnitude instead. So with |Vgs| = 0.6V and |Vth| = 1.022V, the device isn't even close to turning on.\n\nThe subthreshold current of 0.17nA confirms the transistor is off. This suggests the sky130 PFET has a surprisingly high threshold voltage around 1.0V, which seems unusual — I should test with a larger gate-source voltage to verify this behavior.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":584,"cache_read_input_tokens":193553,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":584},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"01e4b3b1-6a11-48e6-b3e7-40758ef8985d","uuid":"188d91aa-6aee-49c7-b412-8a4ae8fa6cb2"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01JcEfqrMEXkA7M38WzD4Vyj","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01TDYSJKP7kvUrE6MnMejKqc","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/home/ubuntu/analog-ai-chips/vibrosense/01_ota/test_pfet.spice","content":"* PFET model verification — sweep Vgs\n.lib \"sky130_minimal.lib.spice\" tt\n\nVdd vdd 0 dc 1.8\nVgs gate 0 dc 0.0\nVds drain 0 dc 0.9\n\n* Test PMOS: source at VDD, drain lower, gate sweeping\nM1 drain gate vdd vdd sky130_fd_pr__pfet_01v8__model W=8u L=1u nf=2\n\n.dc Vgs 0 1.8 0.01\n\n.control\n  run\n  * Find Vth by finding where Id crosses 100nA threshold\n  echo \"Gate voltage vs drain current:\"\n  print @m1[vth]\n  * Plot Id vs Vgs\n  meas dc vth_val find v(gate) when @m1[id]=1e-7 cross=1\n  print vth_val\n  quit\n.endc\n\n.end\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":584,"cache_read_input_tokens":193553,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":584},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"01e4b3b1-6a11-48e6-b3e7-40758ef8985d","uuid":"e3d101fc-f43c-4e10-8466-17d3efb9757a"}
