{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_012yuqaTZGKVMKKccizDUXsg","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Good — the simulation converges! The operating point has issues but now I can diagnose. Key problems:\n\n1. **M9/M10 mirror ratio is 2:1 vs M11** (W/L=2 vs W/L=1), making them carry ~437nA instead of 250nA\n2. **Vout = 0.074V** — pulled low because the NMOS branch takes too much current\n3. **Vbcp = -0.268V** — the PMOS cascode bias circuit is incorrect\n\nLet me fix: use ideal voltage sources for biasing, and resize M9/M10 to W=2u L=4u (W/L=0.5 for 250nA mirror)."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":543,"cache_read_input_tokens":196395,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":543},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"01e4b3b1-6a11-48e6-b3e7-40758ef8985d","uuid":"9a520eeb-ce0a-4c79-b048-38c6764da41f"}
