{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_0148bUVrWejWnwV7CTtkPKJU","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Very interesting! The output jumps from 1.75V at Vbp=0.84 to 0.073V at Vbp=0.86. There's no stable mid-rail operating point with Vbp sweep alone. The circuit has a bi-stable behavior — either the output is near VDD or near VSS.\n\nThis is because the folded cascode has two stable states:\n1. All PMOS delivering current → output high2. All NMOS sinking current → output low\n\nFor a stable mid-rail operating point, the circuit needs:1. \n\nThe PMOS fold current needs to be set by Vbp independent of the output, the NMOS bottom current by Vbn independent of the output, and the input pair should split the tail current equally. The problem is that at the transition point around 0.85V, the PMOS fold current nearly equals the combined current from M9 and M1, so even a tiny change in Vbp flips the output between rails. This suggests improper biasing — likely M3/M4 are entering triode in the high-output state, creating a feedback loop that destabilizes the operating point.\n\nThe core issue appears to be the M12/M13 parallel current sources adding extra current that throws the PMOS side out of balance. Rather than continuing to sweep Vbp, I should try setting up a unity-gain feedback configuration by connecting the output back to the inverting input to automatically regulate the output at the common-mode voltage, then check the operating point to see if the circuit stabilizes better.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1351,"cache_read_input_tokens":211841,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1351},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"01e4b3b1-6a11-48e6-b3e7-40758ef8985d","uuid":"53e96d84-63e5-4e40-a61c-21f7f20aef66"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_0148bUVrWejWnwV7CTtkPKJU","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The output is bi-stable (flips between VDD and VSS). Let me use unity-gain feedback to force the output to mid-rail and check the operating point."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1351,"cache_read_input_tokens":211841,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1351},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"01e4b3b1-6a11-48e6-b3e7-40758ef8985d","uuid":"d525fb12-b721-453c-8ebf-5fafce755e27"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_0148bUVrWejWnwV7CTtkPKJU","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01Dt4znNz1gTnNT9K6JeUmBY","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/home/ubuntu/analog-ai-chips/vibrosense/01_ota/tb_ota_op.spice","content":"* ============================================================\n* TB07: Operating Point Verification — VibroSense OTA\n* Unity-gain feedback to establish mid-rail operating point\n* ============================================================\n\n.lib \"sky130_minimal.lib.spice\" tt\n.include \"ota_foldcasc.spice\"\n\n.param vdd_val = 1.8\n.param vcm_val = 0.9\n\n* Supply\nVdd vdd 0 dc {vdd_val}\nVss vss 0 dc 0\n\n* Bias: diode-connected NMOS for Vbn (matches M11: W=4u L=4u)\nMbn vbn vbn 0 0 sky130_fd_pr__nfet_01v8__model W=4u L=4u nf=1\nIbias vdd vbn dc 500n\n\n* Vbcn: NMOS cascode bias (ideal source, tuned)\nVbcn vbcn 0 dc 0.80\n\n* Vbp: diode-connected PMOS (W=8u L=1u nf=2 matching M3)\nMbp vbp vbp vdd vdd sky130_fd_pr__pfet_01v8__model W=8u L=1u nf=2\nIbp vbp 0 dc 500n\n\n* Vbcp: PMOS cascode bias (ideal source, tuned)\nVbcp vbcp 0 dc 0.70\n\n* Input at common-mode, OUTPUT FEEDS BACK TO INVERTING INPUT\nVinp vinp 0 dc {vcm_val}\n* Unity-gain feedback: vout -> vinn\n* Use a large resistor to ensure DC feedback\nRfb vout vinn 1\n\n* Instantiate OTA\nXota vinp vinn vout vdd vss vbn vbcn vbp vbcp ota_foldcasc\n\n* Load capacitor\nCL vout 0 10p\n\n.op\n.save all\n\n.control\n  run\n\n  echo \"\"\n  echo \"======================================================\"\n  echo \"  OPERATING POINT (Unity-Gain Feedback)\"\n  echo \"======================================================\"\n\n  echo \"--- Bias Voltages ---\"\n  print v(vbn) v(vbcn) v(vbp) v(vbcp) v(vout) v(vinp) v(vinn)\n\n  echo \"--- M1 (NMOS input +) ---\"\n  print @m.xota.m1[id] @m.xota.m1[vgs] @m.xota.m1[vth] @m.xota.m1[vds] @m.xota.m1[vdsat] @m.xota.m1[gm] @m.xota.m1[gds]\n\n  echo \"--- M2 (NMOS input -) ---\"\n  print @m.xota.m2[id] @m.xota.m2[vgs] @m.xota.m2[vth] @m.xota.m2[vds] @m.xota.m2[vdsat] @m.xota.m2[gm] @m.xota.m2[gds]\n\n  echo \"--- M3 (PMOS fold +) ---\"\n  print @m.xota.m3[id] @m.xota.m3[vgs] @m.xota.m3[vth] @m.xota.m3[vds] @m.xota.m3[vdsat] @m.xota.m3[gm] @m.xota.m3[gds]\n\n  echo \"--- M4 (PMOS fold -) ---\"\n  print @m.xota.m4[id] @m.xota.m4[vgs] @m.xota.m4[vth] @m.xota.m4[vds] @m.xota.m4[vdsat] @m.xota.m4[gm] @m.xota.m4[gds]\n\n  echo \"--- M5 (PMOS cascode +) ---\"\n  print @m.xota.m5[id] @m.xota.m5[vgs] @m.xota.m5[vth] @m.xota.m5[vds] @m.xota.m5[vdsat] @m.xota.m5[gm] @m.xota.m5[gds]\n\n  echo \"--- M6 (PMOS cascode -) ---\"\n  print @m.xota.m6[id] @m.xota.m6[vgs] @m.xota.m6[vth] @m.xota.m6[vds] @m.xota.m6[vdsat] @m.xota.m6[gm] @m.xota.m6[gds]\n\n  echo \"--- M7 (NMOS cascode +) ---\"\n  print @m.xota.m7[id] @m.xota.m7[vgs] @m.xota.m7[vth] @m.xota.m7[vds] @m.xota.m7[vdsat] @m.xota.m7[gm] @m.xota.m7[gds]\n\n  echo \"--- M8 (NMOS cascode -) ---\"\n  print @m.xota.m8[id] @m.xota.m8[vgs] @m.xota.m8[vth] @m.xota.m8[vds] @m.xota.m8[vdsat] @m.xota.m8[gm] @m.xota.m8[gds]\n\n  echo \"--- M9 (NMOS current src +) ---\"\n  print @m.xota.m9[id] @m.xota.m9[vgs] @m.xota.m9[vth] @m.xota.m9[vds] @m.xota.m9[vdsat] @m.xota.m9[gm] @m.xota.m9[gds]\n\n  echo \"--- M10 (NMOS current src -) ---\"\n  print @m.xota.m10[id] @m.xota.m10[vgs] @m.xota.m10[vth] @m.xota.m10[vds] @m.xota.m10[vdsat] @m.xota.m10[gm] @m.xota.m10[gds]\n\n  echo \"--- M11 (NMOS tail) ---\"\n  print @m.xota.m11[id] @m.xota.m11[vgs] @m.xota.m11[vth] @m.xota.m11[vds] @m.xota.m11[vdsat] @m.xota.m11[gm] @m.xota.m11[gds]\n\n  echo \"--- M12 (PMOS bias mirror +) ---\"\n  print @m.xota.m12[id] @m.xota.m12[vgs] @m.xota.m12[vth] @m.xota.m12[vds] @m.xota.m12[vdsat] @m.xota.m12[gm] @m.xota.m12[gds]\n\n  echo \"--- M13 (PMOS bias mirror -) ---\"\n  print @m.xota.m13[id] @m.xota.m13[vgs] @m.xota.m13[vth] @m.xota.m13[vds] @m.xota.m13[vdsat] @m.xota.m13[gm] @m.xota.m13[gds]\n\n  echo \"======================================================\"\n\n  echo \"\"\n  echo \"--- Supply Current ---\"\n  print -i(Vdd)\n\n  quit\n.endc\n\n.end\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1351,"cache_read_input_tokens":211841,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1351},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"01e4b3b1-6a11-48e6-b3e7-40758ef8985d","uuid":"4243307d-c20c-4590-a8f1-b9ba041af56f"}
